Regular maintenance, on the other hand, is more reactive. It involves repairing or replacing equipment when it breaks down or experiences an issue. Regular maintenance is done as-needed, rather than on a fixed schedule.

The goal of preventive maintenance is to minimize equipment downtime and extend the lifespan of machinery and assets. Regular maintenance simply restores functionality when something goes wrong.
